Solution Steps:

1. Load the home page with Burp Suite running.
2. Find the GET / request in Proxy → HTTP history and send it to Repeater.
3. Add a cache-buster parameter:
   ?cb=1234
4. Add the header:
   X-Forwarded-Host: example.com
5. Send the request and verify that /resources/js/tracking.js is generated using the X-Forwarded-Host value.
6. Replay the request until the response contains:
   X-Cache: hit
7. On the Exploit Server, change the file path to:
   /resources/js/tracking.js
8. Add the payload:
   alert(document.cookie)
   and store the exploit.
9. Return to the original GET request and remove the cache-buster parameter.
10. Set:
    X-Forwarded-Host: YOUR-EXPLOIT-SERVER-ID.exploit-server.net
11. Keep sending the request until the exploit server URL is reflected in the response and X-Cache: hit is displayed.
12. Open the poisoned URL in the browser and verify that alert(document.cookie) is triggered.
13. If the lab is still unsolved, repeat the poisoning request every few seconds until the victim accesses the cached page.
